        Convert from an IFC STEP file to an ifcOWL file.
        Parameters:
        inputFile - File path of the IFC STEP file.
        outputFile - File path of the output RDF file. RDF syntax is determined by the extension of output file, supported extensions are *.ttl (Turtle) and *.nt (N-Triple).

      • convert

        public void convert(java.lang.String inputFile,
                    java.lang.String outputFile,
                    java.lang.String ifcVersion,
                    java.lang.String baseURI)
             throws java.io.IOException
        Parameters:
        inputFile - File path of the IFC STEP file.
        outputFile - Output file path of the RDF file. RDF syntax is determined by the extension of output file, supported extensions are *.ttl (Turtle) and *.nt (N-Triple).
        ifcVersion - Set the IFC version of the input IFC file, supported IFC versions are IFC2X3_TC1, IFC2X3_FINAL, IFC4, IFC4X1_RC3, IFC4_ADD1 and IFC4_ADD2. If it is null, the converter parses the header in IFC file to automatically determine the IFC version. Only three IFC versions are supported using this way, they are IFC2X3_TC1 (if header contains "IFC2X3"), IFC4x1_RC3 (if header contains "IFC4x1") and IFC4_ADD1 (if header contains "IFC4").
        baseURI - Namespace for the output RDF file, by default it is "http://linkedbuildingdata.net/ifc/resources" + timeLog+"/".
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException

If it is null, the converter parses the header in IFC file to automatically determine the IFC version.       • convert

        public void convert(java.lang.String inputFile,
                    java.lang.String outputFile,
                    java.lang.String ifcVersion,
                    java.lang.String baseURI,
                    boolean logToFile,
                    boolean expid,
                    boolean merge,
                    boolean updateNS)
             throws java.io.IOException
        Parameters:
        inputFile - File path of the IFC STEP file.
        outputFile - Output file path of the RDF file. RDF syntax is determined by the extension of output file, supported extensions are *.ttl (Turtle) and *.nt (N-Triple).
        ifcVersion - Set the IFC version of the input IFC file, supported IFC versions are IFC2X3_TC1, IFC2X3_FINAL, IFC4, IFC4X1_RC3, IFC4_ADD1 and IFC4_ADD2. If it is null, the converter parses the header in IFC file to automatically determine the IFC version. Only three IFC versions are supported using this way, they are IFC2X3_TC1 (if header contains "IFC2X3"), IFC4x1_RC3 (if header contains "IFC4x1") and IFC4_ADD1 (if header contains "IFC4").
        baseURI - Namespace for the output RDF file. If it is null, the default value is "http://linkedbuildingdata.net/ifc/resources" + timeLog+"/".
        logToFile - Set whether log to file, default is false. If it is true, the log file is generated in the same directory of the output file.
        expid - Set whether generate express id as a separate property for instances. Default is false.
        merge - Set whether to remove duplicate objects. Default is false. If it is set to true, the round trip IFC file might have less objects.
        updateNS - Set whether to update namespace for the ifcOWL ontology. Defaut value is false. If it is true, the converter will look up the namespace from the corresponding ifcOWL file in the resources folder and use it. Therefore the corresponding ifcOWL file must be updated before, otherwise it will still use the old namespace.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
